[[Category:OntologySync-managed-resource]]

GCaMP is a fusion protein combining GFP (green fluorescent protein), calmodulin, and the M13 peptide. When intracellular calcium rises (as occurs during neural activity), calmodulin binds calcium and undergoes a conformational change that increases GFP fluorescence. This makes GCaMP the most widely used indicator for calcium imaging in neuroscience.

== Common Variants ==
* '''GCaMP6f''' — fast kinetics, lower sensitivity
* '''GCaMP6s''' — slow kinetics, higher sensitivity
* '''GCaMP7/8''' — newer generations with improved signal-to-noise
* '''jGCaMP8''' — Janelia-optimized variants with faster rise times
